history.content:
I attempted to do that last year, and ended up having to drop 161 due to the workload. 170 + 16B is fine by itself, but not sure if I would recommend 161 on top of that (especially since it has been ramped up since I took the course). 

If you do all of your leetcode/whatever practice over the summer, and then just solely do interviews and stuff during the semester, then it might be doable, but I don't think it's doable if you are also interview prepping. Just my two cents, someone else should answer too!

I am a First Semester Sophomore and I am planning on taking CS 170 + CS 161 + EE 16B + Some UD Humanities P/NP. In addition, I would be recruiting for an internship.

Has someone taken a similar schedule? How manageable/harsh would be the course load?
history.subject: Course load - CS 170 + CS 161 + EE 16B
